	// ---------- Fish Descriptions ----------
	// fish
	"NPCFish.Desc.Abigail": "This weird fish derives sustenance from mountain rocks and minerals.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Alex": "That is one big buff fish!",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Caroline": "This fish nests in the middle of algae which it takes care and feeds off of.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Clint": "It possesses very hard scales with a metallic shine.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Demetrius": "Its elastic scales allows it to resist the harsh sea floor conditions and clean it.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Dwarf": "It used its hardened tentacles to dig through rocks to nest.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Elliott": "The tail of this eel possesses a soft and feathery tip.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Emily": "Under the sun, its iridescent scales shine beautifully.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Evelyn": "It swims just under the surface to enjoy the sun.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.George": "Its round fins allows this sedimentary fish to 'roll' on the sea floor.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Gus": "When it deflates, a curious smell of tomato sauce fills the air.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Haley": "A curious little crab who loves stealing coconuts.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Harvey": "Just holding it in your hands is enough to make you feel in better shape.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Jas": "When seen from behind, its fins look like a beautiful butterfly.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Jodi": "This fish is obssessed with maintaining a clean nesting environnment.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Kent": "Its jaw is lined with hard scales, which it snaps in self-defence.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Krobus": "It's almost impossible to hold it with how intangible it is.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Leah": "The stains on its fins are from crushed corals, which it uses to paint its nest.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Leo": "A unique variant of the blue discus, believed to have been sole responsible of the sandiness of Ginger Island.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Lewis": "It is often found around other fish, enjoying their hard work for itself.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Linus": "Quite nomadic, this little snail's shell holds a very comfortable and transportable nest.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Marnie": "A curious fish that can be seen herding around schools of other fish.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Maru": "Its tentacles can give electric shocks if you touch them.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Pam": "Once out of the water, it exudes a weird ale-like liquid reeking of alcohol.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Penny": "Its dorsal fin has a different, hardback texture.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Pierre": "Its wide jaw is used to carry shinies back to its hoard pile.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Robin": "This peculiar fish builds nests out of pieces of driftwood.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Sam": "It has hardened but soft to the touch dorsal fins.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Sandy": "This fish has flower petals stuck between its scales.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Sebastian": "With how often this fish hides between rocks, it's a miracle you caught it.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Shane": "It uses its tentacles to hide when stressed out.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Vincent": "An energetic little fish who is often found around snails.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Willy": "The fishiest fish to ever fish.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Wizard": "Water seemed disformed around this fish, as if something tried to manipulate it.",
	// crabpot
	"NPCFish.Desc.Bear": "A friend-shaped clam, but beware: it bites.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Birdie": "This curious seaweed seemed to have travelled around the world.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Bouncer": "It bounces, and bounces you back.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Fizz": "It looks at you with the intent of someone having something to sell.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Gourmand": "You found many diverse crops bits and pieces inside this shell.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Governor": "This lobster oversees the region it declared its home.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Grandpa": "You feel a strange sense of pride when looking at it.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Gunther": "Strangely, it looks like it knows a lot of things.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.HatMouse": "Who threw away a perfectly good hat-! Oh wait, that's a living creature.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Henchman": "Its spikes become spikier when you approach its home.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Junimo": "A perlescent friendly creature jumping happily around you.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Marcello": "The creature inside the bottle is clutching a list of books to return.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Mariner": "Even out of the water, it stays wet.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Marlon": "The shell of this creature has dangerous looking, sharp edges.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Morris": "This creature is incessantly trying to give you some sort of coupon.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.MrQi": "Something tells you you shouldn't touch what's inside...",
	"NPCFish.Desc.MrsRaccoon": "It's missing its other half to form a heart.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.SafariGuy": "You had to fight to remove all those snails from this clam.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.Raccoon": "It's missing its other half to form a heart.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.TrashBear": "These big pouches on its body are harmlessly filled with various pieces of trash it collected.",
	"NPCFish.Desc.TravellingMerchant": "Many produces from around the world are stuck on its branches.",

	// ---------- Hint ----------
	"NPCFish.Hint.GenericNote": "I would need more data to acertain this hypothesis, but it seems all those 'weird fish' spotted around the valley share common characteristics with its inhabitants, up to sharing activity periods with our birthdays. This is starting to leave the realm of science I fear.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.CrabpotNote": "I haven't only saw strange fish these days: the other marine creatures are not exampted! Beware of the content of your crab pots and traps, you may have some surprises.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote1": "I thought I saw an amethyst in the water on my way to the mines, but when I tried to catch it, it swam away! And with all those leaves fallen into the lake, I couldn't see what it was. Guess it was one of those \"weird fish\"...",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote2": "There is a weird gurgling sound in my greenhouse. I can't seem to pinpoint its exact location, but I wouldn't be surprised if one of those 'weird fish' had found a way into the pipes.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote3": "I noticed peculiar scales colours in the town river. I think I saw one near Clint's, another on the way to the museum, and two others that moved here and there around town. None of them seemed active in summer.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote4": "I was conducting a field study during the green rain, I saw what I thought to be discarded rubber, but turned out to be a fish of some kind. If anyone captures a specimen I'd be interested seeing it for myself!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote5": "I noticed two new fish in the underground lakes. The fish population is quite scarse there, so it's easy to spot anything unusual.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote6": "While admiring the light bouncing off the surface of the water near my home, I happened to notice an eel-like creature with beautifully striking colors, and the hair perfectly matching the surrounding fall leaves... I've never seen such a dazzling eel before! Perhaps it's one of those 'special fish' Willy was talking about?",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote7": "The secret woods, while scary, are by far prettiest in spring! Last time I went, there were sparkling rainbow colors in the water! I just had to look, but a shape darted off and the colors went with it!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote8": "Of all the scents on Ginger Island, I never expected one to be tomatoes in the ocean! I was too busy tending to the bar to try and catch whatever caused it, but it smells like it would be delicious in a dish! You can never go wrong with salt and tomatoes.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote9": "Recently the fish around the town's waterfall has been more active despite it being Winter. When the fish are most active, I swore I saw glimpses of a 'weird fish' with a big head.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote10": "I saw three curious fish in the Cindersap river: two small ones playing in spring and summer, and a colorful one dragging corals around... It almost looked, 'artistic'.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote11": "This is a note from Joja Plumbing Inc.:\nI had a call from Ms. Jodi about a clogged sink. I tried fixing it, but I thought I saw movement while cleaning the pipes. A similar thing happened when trying to fix the clogged fountain during the heatwave this spring, and the bathhouse's drainage pipe last summer, when it was pouring. Strang things are happening here.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote12": "A strange Tilapia was spotted around Ginger Island during spring. It's normally elusive, but becomes incredibly aggressive during thunderstorms, biting anything invading its territory that seem remotely like a threat.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote13": "I swear there's something new in the sewers! It's shaped like those scary angler fish in the deep sea books, except it doesn't even have the pretty lights... Maybe that's why it seems to look so sad, or maybe it's just freezing?",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote14": "I saw a fish which looked like a Discus, but with... parrot colours? I think? It was a bit weird, I had never seen a fish like this. It darted off as soon as the rain came out though.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote15": "Something has been flopping in and out of my truck at the beginning of the year. It looked like a fish, but I was never able to clearly see it.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote16": "I saw a snail with a yellow shell when foraging at my favourite spot. I have never seen such a shade on any snail before, nor seen one courageous enough to brave the cold.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote17": "Juvinile fish are usually seen being preyed upon by larger ones during fall, but strangely there's a 'weird fish' that's seemingly protecting them in the Forest Lakes...",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote18": "There was a weird octopus in the ocean. I only saw it swam around that one big rock poking out of the water. It scared me when I tried to go swimming!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote19": "The little grotto on Ginger Island during spring somehow smells more like alcohol than usual... Could've sworn it came from the water, but I still saw a fish in there. I don't think normal fish can survive in alcohol...",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote20": "Weird creatures are expected in the Mutant Bug Lair, but I think I found a new one this spring after dropping a coin in the water... Some weird looking fish snatched it up instantly!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote21": "Hardwood is so abundant in the Secret Woods, but last fall, I could've sworn I saw a 'weird fish' swim away with the branches that accidentally fell in the water. I thought they would be too heavy for it to carry!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote22": "There's a weird lionfish spotted at the beach during summer, how did that get here all the way from ginger island? It doesn't look like a regular lionfish either... Maybe it's a part of it's migration route.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote23": "I went to visit Sandy on her birthday, and in the pond I saw a 'weird fish' that reminded me of her! It had the same pink colors, but it swam away before Sandy could notice it!",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote24": "I was drinking on the deck by the pond, when I saw a shadow in the water. I think it was a squid or something? I left because it was raining, and it blew ink as soon as I moved.",
	"NPCFish.Hint.FishNote25": "I sensed a disturbance in the dark tunnel north of the railroad. I wouldn't be surprised if those… 'weird fish' were the cause of it. Snowfalls wouldn't be enough of a reason.",

	// ---------- Quests, Dialogues, and Events ----------
	// Introduction quest
	"NPCFish.WillyQuest_title": "A weird fish?",
	"NPCFish.WillyQuest_content": "Willy told you about a strange fish \"that looked like him\", which he saw at the beach by his house.\nYou should try to catch it - even just to see if it does exist.",

	// Willy's event
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line1": "Ahoy ${lad^lass^kid}$...",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_question1": "He looks concerned.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_question1response1": "Are you ok?",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_question1response2": "What's wrong?",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line2": "I'll ask you to trust me on this one.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line3": "There is a... weird fish, that looks like me, over by the beach.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line4": "It had a beret and a fishing rod!",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line5": "That's not a joke! And yes, I was as sober as one can be!",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line6": "Listen ${lad^lass^kid}$. That fish genuinely scares me.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line7": "I came to ask you to catch it for me.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line8": "You've become quite the good angler now!",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_line9": "Anyway. If you do catch it... Honestly I don't care, I don't want to see it.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_fadeline1": "He looked really distraught.",
	"NPCFish.WillyEvent_fadeline2": "A weird fish that looked like Willy? You're really curious to see it, if it exists!",

	// Letter
	"NPCFish.LewisLetter": "Greetings @.\n\nI concur Willy told you about the \"weird fish\" he spotted? He told everyone actually, even told us you caught it. Honestly, congrats.\n\nHe had setup a book in his house so we can all report sighting of this fish, but it ended up being filled with sightings of a lot of *different* weird fish.\nDon't bother going however: it mysteriously disappeared the other day. I think I heard Penny said she spotted one of the pages torn from it and floating in the wind... You might find them all around the valley.\n\nIf you want to go and try to catch them all, well... We'll all be quite happy. These strange fish are scaring everyone!\n\n- Lewis"

	// Fish CT
}
